HOUSE BILL 679
R1 5lr3308
By: Delegate Grammer
Introduced and read first time: January 24, 2025
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Transportation Authority – Patapsco River Toll Bridge – Design
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Transportation Authority to design and locate
4 the entrances and exits to the new bridge over the Patapsco River to ensure that a
5 vehicle that does not cross the bridge is not required to pay a toll; and generally
6 relating to toll bridges.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Transportation
9 Section 4–408
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Transportation
15 4–408.
16 THE AUTHORITY SHALL DESIGN AND LOCATE THE ENTRANCES AND EXITS TO
17 THE NEW BRIDGE OVER THE PATAPSCO RIVER THAT WILL REPLACE THE
18 COLLAPSED FRANCIS SCOTT KEY BRIDGE, AND THE ASSOCIATED ROADS, TO
19 ENSURE THAT A VEHICLE THAT WILL NOT CROSS THE BRIDGE IS NOT REQUIRED TO
20 PAY A TOLL.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
22 October 1, 2025.
